{
  "stem": "11290.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But the irony is that because there was large preparation for war-- Germany made at that time already, also they were hiding it-- led to the fact that people like us had merchandise and had merchandise to sell, and we're actually-- the business was actually prospering.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Woolen, woolen material, woolen mostly for men's clothing, woolen cloth.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] So the business was really prospering, more or less, until Kristallnacht 1938 when it became obvious that it was impossible to carry on.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was already in the United States.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, well, the preparations, of course, took, took in much of-- took up much of my time.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I had to go, first of all, to the American consul, which means days of waiting until one's number was called and then to be interviewed.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In those days, the, the, the-- there were not such masses of immigrants-- or emigrants-- yet, as were in later years because it was comparatively early, in 1934.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And in 19-- before I left in 1936, Germany [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] tore up the Treaty of Versailles and started, against the treaty rules, to get-- to get-- to get militarized.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In fact, they marched into the demilitarized zone on the Rhineland.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And from then on, there was a, an order out from Hitler that nobody could leave.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "No German man could leave Germany without getting a release from the military command in his area.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was 28 years old.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But they didn't take any Jews in the army.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But still, they-- in order-- when they wanted to leave the-- anybody who wanted to leave the country had to get this permission.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
